==English==
===Verb===
'''hast'''

# ''(archaic, poetic, religious)'' you have; second person singular of ''[[have]]'', used with pronoun ''[[thou]]'':
#: "Thou hast lovely eyes!"
#: "Thou hast gone from me."

: '''hast''' is the original second person singular of ''[[have]]'', now archaic but still found in poetry, older and religious works, corresponding to the familiar second person in some other European languages.  It is used both as a main verb and an auxiliary verb.

